##Memories of Tomorrow Online photo exhibition

Micro Signal Anti

Features A2n, Anti-2019-ncov. A group of folk volunteers whose main work is to popularize science and dispel rumors.

Recollections
February 13,2020
The A2N epidemic volunteer group initiated one of the in-depth content projects
"memory of tomorrow" online photo exhibition

Freeze time with the camera
To record the day's joys and sorrows
To give tomorrow the strength to move on

A total of 10 entries were selected for the fourth issue
The duration of the exhibition is unlimited
Please arrange your own viewing time
Orderly entrance

"curators"
A2n Volunteer Group Photo Line Exhibition Group
Jessie Jia, Fu Fu, Baa Yang, Xiao An, Miya, Dan Qing

"Exhibitor"
Min Min, Su Ruiqi, Xiao Xiao, Xie Yutong, Yang Yaru,
Zhang Linsong, Zhang Yuanhang, Chang Chen, Zoe

2020

Spring is here
Willow early yellow light, hydrology new green micro
As the epidemic spread, everything began
Go China! Go Wuhan! Go Together!

A Song for spring

The epidemic will end

Chang Chen
Feb 13th 2020 | Wuhan, Hubei Province
Click to see the story behind it
▼
Gengzi Year Wuhan
A pregnant yellow cat
I don't quite understand why
These humans aren't dressed the way they're supposed to be
All wear "masks" to cover their faces
It doesn't really matter
The point is, it's easy to get food
Seems to be getting a little tense lately
In order to survive with the belly of the baby
I had to prop myself up
Trying to find something to eat in the blue "lunch box. "

Buying vegetables
Chang Chen
January 27,2020, Wuhan, Hubei
Click to see the story behind it
▼
Gengzi Year Wuhan
January 27th
A few days'siege
Has made it difficult for citizens to shop normally
The supermarket is crowded
To avoid cross-contamination,
Some citizens found the closed market next to the path
Looking for fresh vegetables from nearby farmers'homes
People are rushing to buy food
The background is a "No illegal stall-setting" banner
The market manager at the moment
Or where he went
Shoppers and vendors
It's the best of both worlds

A good-bye
Zoe
Feb 5th 2020 | Moscow
Click to see the story behind it
▼
Traveling in Russia at the height of the outbreak
After two canceled flights,
To buy a plane ticket home from Moscow
All china-bound passengers are now en route to Terminal F
Everyone was surprisingly quiet
The duty-free shop is a long line for masks
It was the last sunset I saw in Russia
We don't know how long the next one's GonNa take
To See this lovely place all over again

The A2N outbreak volunteer team is
For COVID-19 pneumonia
Group of civilian volunteers
Dedicated to the dissemination of true and valuable information

To get people to see what's really going on
To better resist the virus, reduce infection
Accurate knowledge of the epidemic
To collect up-to-date and reliable information on the situation
Crush rumors and spread true and valuable information

If you and I want the same thing,

Reach out to us and work with us through the hard times
"If there is no torch after that
I am the only light."

@ A2n to fight new coronavirus
